</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
</IN>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian steel production totaled 159,248 metric
tons in the week ended Saturday, up 0.4% from 158,653 tons in
the preceding week but down 46% from 286,816 tons a year
earlier, Statistics Canada, a federal agency, said.
   The drop from the 1989 pace is partly attributable to an
ongoing strike at Stelco Inc., a steel concern.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The cumulative total in 1990 was 9,421,764 tons, down 16%
from 11,143,714 tons a year earlier.
