   WASHINGTON -- McDonnell Douglas Corp. received an $836.4
million Air Force contract for F-15E aircraft.
   The F-15E, the company's most sophisticated jet fighter,
has the ability to attack targets on the ground from long
range. Work on the contract is to be completed in May 1992.
                                                                                                       

