</IN>
<LP>
   Ogden Corp. ended speculation that it might split into two
public companies, and said it intends to retain its 85%
holding in Ogden Projects Inc., its waste-to-energy unit.
   Odgen, based in New York, also announced a major
reshuffling of the Ogden Projects board, replacing five of
its eight members and adding three others.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Earlier this year, Ogden had been discussing the possible
creation of Ogden Projects as a separate entity.
   Ogden Projects, which went public in 1989, has been
growing rapidly as it brings on line large waste-to-energy
