had 13 plants in operation, 7 under construction, and 6
awaiting license.
   Ogden's other major activity is a broad array of service
business which generated $1 billion of revenue in 1989,
ranging from asbestos abatement, managing arenas and
convention centers, and operating commercial aviation
facilities to managing industrial and building locations and
providing building maintenance services.
   For the six months, Ogden Projects had net income of $15.9
million, or 45 cents a share, on revenue of $189 million.
