   Marketing Brief -- MGM/UA Communications Co.:
   Pathe Communications Adds
   Payment Toward Purchase
</HL>
<DATE>
09/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6
</SO>
<CO>
   MGM PCC
</CO>
<IN>
RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)
MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   MGM/UA Communications Co. said it received checks totaling
$50 million from Pathe Communications Corp., bringing to $353
million the amount Pathe has paid in cash toward its proposed
$1.3 billion acquisition of MGM/UA.
   The payment is the last in a series of good-faith interim
payments required under the companies' merger agreement.
Pathe, based in Beverly Hills, Calif., has also given MGM/UA
a $75 million security interest in three films slated by
Pathe.
</LP>
